%N A396001 Largest number of terms in greedy Egyptian fraction expansion of k/n for 1 <= k <= n with GCD(n,k) = 1.
%C A396001 For n >= 2, a(n) is the maximum of A050205(n,k) with k restricted to numbers that are coprime to n. The smallest n for which the restriction to coprime k makes a difference is n = 58: A050205(58,k) <= 5 for all k except k = 54, which is not coprime to 58.
%C A396001 The smallest n >= 2 such that a(n) = m is A395231(m).
%H A396001 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A396001/b396001.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
